 and the Canadian documentary tradition. Varga illuminates how the film can be viewed through the lens of Harold Innis&apos;s theories of communication and culture, opening up the work of this great Canadian political economist to film studies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aMotion pictureszCanadaxHistory. 4aDISCOUNT-B. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144266438840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442664388423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781442664388.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MUAR  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK